INSTRUCTIONS:

This instruction assumes that you have:
0) installed Android SDK, Android NDK.
1) compiled VES (including VTK, KiwiViewer) for Android (http://vtk.org/Wiki/VES/Developers_Guide) 
2) compiled Point Cloud Library for Android in conjunction with VTK, VES, and Kiwi (http://vtk.org/Wiki/VES/Point_Cloud_Library)

Steps
1st - patch VES Library, rebuild VES library.

cd PATH_TO_VES_DIR 
git apply vesKiwi.patch

2nd - copy KiwiPCL to PATH_TO_VES_DIR/Apps/Android

Change dependencies in the next files:

CMakeLists.txt

Replace all “/home/andrey/kiwi/VES/” to your path to VES library.
Replace all “/home/andrey/kiwi/pcl-superbuild/” to your path to PCL for Android in conjunction with VTK, VES, and Kiwi  
Replace “/home/andrey/android-ndk-r8b/” to your path to android-ndk

configure_ant.sh
Replace “/home/andrey/android-sdks/” to your path to android-sdk

configure_cmake.sh
Replace “/home/andrey/android-ndk-r8b/” to your path to android-ndk

tools.sh
Replace all “/home/andrey/kiwi/VES/” to your path to VES library.

build/my.sh
Replace all “/home/andrey/kiwi/VES/” to your path to VES library.
Replace all “/home/andrey/kiwi/pcl-superbuild/” to your path to PCL for Android in conjunction with VTK, VES, and Kiwi  

assets.cmake
Replace all “/home/andrey/kiwi/VES/” to your path to VES library.


Next, from this directory execute the following commands:

# configure
./configure_ant.sh
./configure_cmake.sh

# build
./compile.sh

# run on a device
./run.sh
